Carlton Tavern was bulldozed by developers in Maida Vale, west London . 
  Landlady Patsy Lord was told to close for an ' inventory' but returned two days later to find the pub was no longer standing . 
  It was the only building in the road not destroyed by Hitler's bombs during the Blitz . 
  Developers CLTX Ltd was denied planning permission to turn it into luxury flats . 
  Historic England was due to mark the pub as a listed building . 
  Red Dwarf actor Danny John-Jules blasted the demolition as 'another nail in the coffin' Westminster City Council is considering legal action against developers . 
 